---
title: Pork Cutlets in Grape & Thyme Pan Sauce with Roasted Carrots & Potato Wedges
description: This meal is perfect proof that grapes belong on the dinner table—in the form of a sweet, savory, aromatic pan sauce. They’re simmered with shallot, fresh thyme, chicken stock, Dijon mustard, and lemon juice until the sauce is thick and jammy; then, it’s all spooned over seared pork cutlets and served with roasted carrots and potato wedges. Prepare for the oohs and ahhs from your seriously impressed dinner companions, because this is a sauce to remember.
